# mctoolbox Project Context

This project is a Python library for real-time tuning of Microchip MCAF motor control firmware via X2Cscope.

The full specification is in [SPEC.md](../../SPEC.md). Read it before making architectural decisions or adding new modules.

Key points:
- Uses `pyx2cscope` (pyX2Cscope) as the communication layer -- do not reimplement LNet or ELF parsing
- All tuning is at runtime via X2Cscope variable reads/writes -- no firmware recompilation
- Q-format conversion uses `parameters.json` from the motorBench project
- Test harness guard key `0xD1A6` must be set before test modes; guard timeout must be refreshed periodically
- Phase 1 is library-only (Python scripts / Jupyter); Phase 2 adds a cross-platform GUI
- Python 3.12, baud rate default 115200 (configurable)
